<item>
            <title>[FLINK-15518] Don&apos;t hide web frontend side pane automatically</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15518</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-13386&quot; title=&quot;Fix some frictions in the new default Web UI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-13386&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-13386&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the side pane hides automatically in some cases but not all cases. When I was debugging or trying the web frontend I found this behaviour a bit disconcerting. Could we disable the hiding by default? The user can still manually hide if they want to.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
